<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Saxifraga</i> <i>nidifica</i> is characteristically present in the herbaceous layer with <i>Antennaria</i> <i>media</i>, <i>Mimulus</i> <i>rubellus</i>, <i>Polygonum</i> <i>minimum</i>, <i>Potentilla</i> <i>drummondii</i>, <i>Rhodiola</i> <i>integrifolia</i>, <i>Saxifraga</i> <i>bryophora</i>, <i>Sedum</i> <i>obtusatum</i> and <i>Selaginella</i> <i>watsonii</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 30 cm; cover is open. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Rock crevices, toe slopes, bare sandy or loamy substrates, and unstable moving scree where snow remains on the ground until July or later. Patterned ground features are common. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Saxifraga nidifica</i> as a FACW plant. </div>
</div>

		
